Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Handle at neck join. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine buff; cream slip.
Production date: 181 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.163, 31]. Name Agemachos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0883)
